# One Dev Server Rule (Strict)

- HARD REQUIREMENT: exactly one dev server process for this project at any time.
- Before starting a server, MUST check whether one is already running and reuse it.
- If any duplicate exists, MUST stop duplicates first, then start one clean instance.
- Prefer default URL/port unless user explicitly requests otherwise.
- After any restart, report exactly one active URL.

## Required Workflow

1. Stop duplicates first (`vite`, `npm run dev`, equivalent watchers for this app).
2. Start exactly one server instance.
3. Confirm the final active local URL and share only that URL.

## Forbidden

- Starting a second dev server “just in case”.
- Keeping multiple ports active for the same app (e.g. `5173` and `5174` together).
- Starting a new server without first checking existing processes/terminals.
